Package: flight-hub
Version: {{VERSION}}
Section: games
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31), libdbus-1-3, libudev1
Recommends: rtkit
Maintainer: OpenFlight Team <contact@openflight.dev>
Homepage: https://github.com/EffortlessMetrics/OpenFlight
Description: Flight Hub daemon for flight simulation input management
 Flight Hub provides unified control for flight controls, panels,
 and force feedback devices across MSFS, X-Plane, and DCS simulators
 with real-time 250Hz axis processing.
 .
 Features:
  - Real-time 250Hz axis processing with <5ms p99 latency
  - Multi-simulator support (MSFS, X-Plane, DCS)
  - Support for Saitek/Logitech, Thrustmaster, VKB, Virpil, and Winwing devices
  - Force feedback safety systems with proper interlocks
  - Auto-profile switching based on aircraft detection
  - Panel and StreamDeck integration with rule-based LED control
